g.text: Outbox Worker Pool Architecture + Data Flow

ul.li: Coordinator: polls every 2s, sends rows to buffered channel
Workers (3): drain channel, publish, mark published
FOR UPDATE SKIP LOCKED: safe for multiple coordinator replicas
Channel capacity = 50: matches LIMIT 50 fetch; backpressure on slow workers
Error path: Publish fail row stays NULL retried next cycle
At-least-once: if MarkPublished fails after Publish, row re-published

div.p: SELECT id, event_type, payload FROM outbox WHERE published_at IS NULL ORDER BY created_at ASC LIMIT 50 FOR UPDATE SKIP LOCKED
FOR UPDATE SKIP LOCKED Prevents concurrent coordinators from double-publishing the same row
Row remains in unpublished state re-fetched next 2s cycle
